	<div class="How we Treat" id="HowweTreat?">
	<h2>How we Treat?</h2>
	The City Hospital's Institute of Neurosciences uses a comprehensive and multidisciplinary 
	approach for every patient. Our integrated team of neurologists, neurosurgeons, 
	interventional neuro-radiologists and physical therapists work with the latest technologies 
	like precision-guided MRI surgery to treat brain and spinal disorders. Our doctors combine modern
	 medicine with Ayurveda to find new ways of treating patients with minimal possible trauma.
	  Complementary therapies have been adopted for various movement disorders like Parkinson’s, 
	  Stroke Rehabilitation and several types of post-operative therapy. City Hospital has advanced 
	  technologies including the CyberKnife VSI Robotic Radiosurgery System, 
	  ‘Brain Suite’ Miyabi intra-operative MRI OT, 
	  Intra-operative O-Arm Spine Suite and other advanced neuro-imaging techniques along 
	  with dedicated neurosurgery and neurology ICUs. We select what modality would be best for 
	  any given patient from the range of treatment capabilities in neurosciences.
